        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 12 at 3:25PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 324 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles south of Greenville Downtown, or near Piedmont, moving
southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Piedmont, Williamston, West Pelzer, Donaldson Center, Powdersville,
West Greenville, and Fork Shoals.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
